list.name: Default
list.comment:
Set up initial creation of life, boost, and lazar bars to be based off initial variable. This will allow input at the creation of StatusLayer to allow custom start values.
Implemented GameOverLayer, still needs work.

task.summary: Default task
Integrated moving background and attempt at making buttons functional.
Adding Images
Created method for adding background objects and working on random creation of objects
Adding background objects (Star only at this point) seems to be working theoretically with no visual verification.
Tweaked background image insertion and refresh. To work on y-plane later
Worked on applying impulse on hitting an object
Integrated mid sky loading Integrated maths for moving camera on y axis.
Integrated top and transition sky loading Updated maths for moving camera on y axis.
Made distance label functional
Put a back wall at beginning Set up moving of background if character starts going backward Fixed boost and lazar label locations
Beginning to add slingshot object and joint for launch
Came up with solution for initial launch touch tracking and preventing screen from updating until prelaunch is finished

A little better implementation of slingshot. Changed Stars to be more realstic and be on random y axis. Added and fixed names of resources
At some point I messed up my vertical location and camera work. Need to make a global variable that fixes that
Moved numbers around a bit to make sky translation look smooth again. Made semi-constants and adjusted numbers to make stars/background objects show up in the right places.
Added kegs and implemented plan for placing ground objects on the ground.

Initial implementation of ground, needs work. Adjusted ground height and fixed some equations to work correctly related to ground height, not just by luck. Removed invisible ground object. Added lava and quicksand. Added ground objects to BackgroundObject class. Moved Math.Random() to initialization of the game so it is not being called every time new objects are added, which should reduce CPU utilization.
Only update distance meter when moving forward and in a position positive from the slingshot.
Fixed mistaken deleted semi-colon in PlayScene. Implemented better launch mechanism using a static image when grabbed by user and back to physical body when released.
Fixed debug node to show physics object outlines
More work on rope.
Restored only physics objects for launch and integrated rope disconnect.
Figured how to update character position every update while touch event in progress.
A little more rope fine tuning
Temporary solution for launch rope
Added quicksand. Implemented friction a bit. Prevented rotation of main character.
Integrated Trampoline and Spikewall. Integrated debug autolaunch option for when I don't want to manually launch character or when rdp doesn't work for some reason.
Adding resources for bomb, spikewall, and trampoline(now that I know how to in WebStorm)

Small adjustments to background objects. Trying to make ramp have some forward velocity. Changed momentum of character and rope segments to infinity to prevent them from rotating.
Added return false to sensor begin collisions so they will not continue to calculate collision physics. Added life and boost updates to sensors. Integrated impact collision life adjustments. Integrated no forward movement life reduction.
